== 詞源和術語 ==
部分說法認為，因為絕大部分人的[[性别指定|性别指定]]與[[性別認同|性別認同]]是相同的，因此無須以「順」字強調之。但對於跨性別者甚至非異性戀者而言，大部分人皆為順性別，並不代表順性別是理所當然的；使用「順」字強調的目的即在於，破除「人人皆為順性別」的預設。

儘管一些人認為順性別一詞就只是[[政治正確|政治正確]]的用語，<ref name="International">{{cite web|title=What's Your Choice – Male, Female, Transgender, Intersex?: Other Gender Options Now Available for Facebook Users|url=http://www.ibtimes.com.au/whats-your-choice-male-female-transgender-intersex-other-gender-options-now-available-facebook-users|date=2014-02-14|quote=|last1=Hernandez|first1=Vittorio|website=[[International_Business_Times|International Business Times]]|access-date=2015-12-18|archive-date=2015-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222165716/http://www.ibtimes.com.au/whats-your-choice-male-female-transgender-intersex-other-gender-options-now-available-facebook-users|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Telegraph">{{cite news|last=Daubney|first=Martin|date=2014-12-16|title=Was 2014 the year political correctness went stark raving mad?: This year has seen political correctness turn sinister, thanks to the outraged, sanctimonious reactions of social media's PC police, argues Martin Daubney|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11294974/Was-2014-the-year-political-correctness-went-stark-raving-mad.html|newspaper=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|location=|access-date=|archive-date=2020-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922023915/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11294974/Was-2014-the-year-political-correctness-went-stark-raving-mad.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Spectator">{{cite magazine|last=Thompson|first=Damian|date=February 7, 2015|title=The march of the new political correctness|url=http://new.spectator.co.uk/2015/02/the-march-of-the-new-political-correctness/|magazine=[[The_Spectator|The Spectator]]|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151004073230/http://new.spectator.co.uk/2015/02/the-march-of-the-new-political-correctness/|archive-date=2015-10-04|access-date=2017-11-08|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="CBC">{{cite web|title='Mansplaining' the return of political correctness:The scourge of the '90s, PC seems to be gaining a new foothold on college campuses|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/mansplaining-the-return-of-political-correctness-1.2999060|date=2015-03-17|quote=|last1=Macdonald|first1=Neil|website=[[CBC.ca|CBC.ca]]|access-date=2015-12-18|archive-date=2015-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150318114557/http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/mansplaining-the-return-of-political-correctness-1.2999060|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Spectator2">{{cite magazine|last=Wordsworth|first=Dot|date=November 7, 2015|title=How we ended up 'cisgender':The history of a tendentious word|url=http://new.spectator.co.uk/2015/11/how-we-ended-up-cisgender/|magazine=[[The_Spectator|The Spectator]]|location=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151112200858/http://new.spectator.co.uk/2015/11/how-we-ended-up-cisgender/|archivedate=November 12, 2015|access-date=|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>但醫學學者自1990年代以來就一直使用該術語並認識到其在跨性別研究中的重要性。<ref name="Aultman">{{cite journal|title=Cisgender|last=Aultman|first=B|journal=TSQ: Transgender Studies Quarterly|issue=1–2|doi=10.1215/23289252-2399614|year=2014|volume=1|page=61|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref name="Psychology & Psychiatry Journal">{{cite journal|title=Re-assessing the Role of Gender-Related Cognitions for Self-Esteem: The Importance of Gender Typicality for Cisgender Adults|url=|first1=Charlotte Chucky|last2=Bettergarcia|first2=Jay N.|date=2015|journal=Psychology & Psychiatry Journal|issue=5–6|doi=10.1007/s11199-015-0458-0|volume=72|pages=221–236|last3=Brent|first3=Lindsay M.|access-date=|last1=Tate}}</ref><ref name="Mental Health Weekly Digest">{{cite journal|title=New Mental Health Study Findings Have Been Reported by Investigators at Brown University (Gender Minority Stress, Mental Health, and Relationship Quality: A Dyadic Investigation of Transgender Women and Their Cisgender Male Partners)|url=|date=2015|journal=Mental Health Weekly Digest|volume=9|pages=224|access-date=}}</ref>

2014年2月，[[Facebook|Facebook]]開始提供「自定義」的性別選項，用戶可以從性別相關的選項當中選擇一個或多個與性別相關的術語，包含順性別等等。<ref>{{cite web|title=Facebook goes beyond 'male' and 'female' with new gender options|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/02/13/tech/social-media/facebook-gender-custom/index.html|accessdate=2014-02-13|author=Brandon Griggs|date=2014-02-13|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308155048/https://www.cnn.com/2014/02/13/tech/social-media/facebook-gender-custom/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Facebook's New Gender Identity Options|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/facebooks-new-gender-identity-options|author=The Associated Press|accessdate=2020-08-13|archive-date=2014-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222220022/http://bigstory.ap.org/article/facebooks-new-gender-identity-options|dead-url=no}}</ref>順性別還於2013年被添加到《[[牛津英語詞典|牛津英語詞典]]》中，其定義為「指一个人的身份认同感与出生时的指定性别相对应的人（与[[跨性別|跨性別]]相反）」。<ref>{{cite web|title=New words notes June 2015|url=http://public.oed.com/the-oed-today/recent-updates-to-the-oed/june-2015-update/new-words-notes-june-2015/|accessdate=2015-08-02|publisher=Oxford University Press|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150814051905/http://public.oed.com/the-oed-today/recent-updates-to-the-oed/june-2015-update/new-words-notes-june-2015/|archivedate=2015-08-14|last1=Martin|first1=Katherine|website=Oxford English Dictionary|url-status=dead}}</ref>[[美國歷史學會|美國歷史學會]]指出，自从术语順性別被纳入以来，該術語的使用已經越來越普遍。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Tracing Terminology {{!}} Perspectives on History {{!}} AHA|url=https://www.historians.org/publications-and-directories/perspectives-on-history/may-2017/tracing-terminology-researching-early-uses-of-cisgender|website=www.historians.org|access-date=2019-08-01|archive-date=2021-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514144840/https://www.historians.org/publications-and-directories/perspectives-on-history/may-2017/tracing-terminology-researching-early-uses-of-cisgender|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 批評 ==

=== 從女性主義和性別研究 ===
Krista Scott-Dixon在2009年寫道：「我更喜歡non-trans（非跨）這個詞，以及其他選擇，像是cissexual或cisgendered。」<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Public health, private parts: A feminist public-health approach to trans issues|last=Scott-Dixon|first=Krista|authorlink=Krista Scott-Dixon|journal=Hypatia|issue=3|doi=10.1111/j.1527-2001.2009.01044.x|year=2009|volume=24|pages=33–55}}</ref>她認同這個觀點是因為她認為術語「non-trans」這個詞對普通人來説更爲明白，使得幫助跨性別個體正常化。

女性和性別研究學者Mimi Marinucci寫道，有些人認為「跨性別、順性別」的二元性與「[[男性化|男性化]]、[[女性化|女性化]]」的[[性別二元論|性別二元論]]一樣危險或自欺欺人，因為它與跨性別者相反，並且任意地將認同自己為女同性戀、男同性戀或雙性戀（LGB）的人混為一談，對於一個[[異性戀主義|異性戀主義]]的人來說過於簡單化了。非跨性别人士（non-trans）可能会提出疑問，因為將LGB個體與異性戀放在一起表明LGB个体与跨性别者不同，可能代表「LGB个体的[[性別認同|性別認同]]和[[性別表現|性別表現]]的經歷與文化對他們的期望沒有任何的不相容」。<ref>{{cite book|last=Marinucci|first=Mimi|publisher=Zed Books|year=2010|title=Feminism is Queer: The Intimate Connection between Queer and Feminist Theory|url=https://archive.org/details/feminismisqueeri00mari|url-access=limited|pages=[https://archive.org/details/feminismisqueeri00mari/page/n141 125]–126}}</ref>

=== 來自雙性人組織 ===
{{See also|雙性人}}
雙性人天生就具有非典型的生理性别特征，這可能會使最初的[[性別指定|性別指定]]複雜化並導致不自主或強制的醫療。<ref name="Dreger">{{cite book|last=Domurat Dreger|first=Alice|title=Hermaphrodites and the Medical Invention of Sex|year=2001|publisher=Harvard University Press|location=USA|isbn=978-0-674-00189-3}}</ref><ref name="jointun">[http://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/publications/gender_rights/eliminating-forced-sterilization/en/ Eliminating forced, coercive and otherwise involuntary sterilization, An interagency statement] {{Wayback|url=http://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/publications/gender_rights/eliminating-forced-sterilization/en/ |date=20150711130919 }}, [[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]], May 2014.</ref>根據interACT倡導者的說法，儘管有雙性人使用這個詞，順性別這個術語可能會讓有雙性人特徵的人「感到困惑」。<ref>[http://interactyouth.org/post/97343969730/inter-act-has-been-working-with-mtvs-faking-it-on Inter/Act Youth • Inter/Act has been working with MTV's Faking It on...] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140916025255/http://interactyouth.org/post/97343969730/inter-act-has-been-working-with-mtvs-faking-it-on|date=September 16, 2014}} [[Interact_Advocates_for_Intersex_Youth|Inter/Act Youth]]. Retrieved October 17, 2014.</ref>「雙性人平權運動」人士Hida Viloria指出，作为一个天生拥有雙性人身體的人，TA的性别认同感是非二元性的，感覺與TA的身體一致，這使得TA天生即是順性別又是[[非二元性別|非二元性別]]，但是根據順性別的定義，與[[非二元性別|非二元性別]]可能是对立的，这证明了这个词的基础是一个二元性别模型，而这个模型并不能解释雙性人的存在。TA还批评了「出生時指定性別」一詞在順性別者的定義中被使用，卻沒有註意到嬰兒在世界大多數地區都被指定為男性或女性，而不考慮世界上的雙性人地位，並且指出這樣做混淆了雙性人的誕生並在男性或女性的二元性別基礎中構建了性別認同，以及未能解釋某些天生雙性人的性別認同是非二元的存在。除此之外還有對雙性人基於性別的歧視，說明其為產後性別特徵而不是性別認同或表現，就如同「正常化」嬰兒生殖器手術一樣。<ref>[http://hidaviloria.com/caught-in-the-gender-binary-blind-spot-intersex-erasure-in-cisgender-rhetoric/ Caught in the Gender Binary Blind Spot: Intersex Erasure in Cisgender Rhetoric] {{Wayback|url=http://hidaviloria.com/caught-in-the-gender-binary-blind-spot-intersex-erasure-in-cisgender-rhetoric/ |date=20201112023646 }}, [[Hida_Viloria|Hida Viloria]], August 18, 2014. Retrieved October 17, 2014.</ref>

